1
00:00:00,541 --> 00:00:04,250
After I completed four months in prison

2
00:00:06,875 --> 00:00:09,416
The interrogator came to me and opened the shutter

3
00:00:09,541 --> 00:00:11,833
He said, Come here! What’s your name? I answered him

4
00:00:12,916 --> 00:00:15,916
He asked, How long have you been here? I said, Four months

5
00:00:16,666 --> 00:00:18,791
He said, Fine, you’ve been here too long, we’ll release you

6
00:00:19,875 --> 00:00:23,208
And you must tell your father to come back

7
00:00:23,333 --> 00:00:27,916
Because by escaping, he proved the charge against himself

8
00:00:28,666 --> 00:00:31,541
I said, Since you’re sure he’s innocent

9
00:00:31,666 --> 00:00:34,250
Why did he stay three months until he had to escape

10
00:00:35,125 --> 00:00:37,500
Why didn’t you release him then?

11
00:00:39,916 --> 00:00:44,916
He said, The point is to tell him to
come back, there’s nothing against him

12
00:00:45,125 --> 00:00:50,541
Better than traveling to Azaz, Qamishli, or Turkey

13
00:00:51,250 --> 00:00:52,375
I said, God willing

14
00:00:52,458 --> 00:00:53,458
So I could get out of prison afterward

15
00:00:54,791 --> 00:00:56,541
Before leaving, I asked about my brother, and he said

16
00:00:56,666 --> 00:00:59,958
He must pay 10,000 dollars to be released

17
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:04,750
Plus another 10,000 dollars for my cousin

18
00:01:05,916 --> 00:01:09,208
The interrogator told me that once they had received the money

19
00:01:09,416 --> 00:01:10,583
They would release them immediately

20
00:01:10,708 --> 00:01:14,333
So I secured the amount for my brother that night

21
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:17,500
And I went to them after Maghrib prayer

22
00:01:17,791 --> 00:01:19,791
Right after I had secured the money

23
00:01:20,625 --> 00:01:24,291
But they didn’t receive me and told me to come back the next day

24
00:01:24,791 --> 00:01:27,250
Because there were no visits at night

25
00:01:27,875 --> 00:01:28,875
So I came back the next day

26
00:01:30,375 --> 00:01:32,208
I handed over the money, and my brother was released
